Neat. I like the concept, but a few of the things you say in the article could mesh a little better. To begin with you say that the item can be stored anywhere outside with no problem. Later you say that if both doors are opened, then water will continue to flow out until an equal pressure situation is reached outside. Seems to me that the safest way to store this SCP would be in a sealed room that is already filled with water. That way one or both of the doors can be opened at any time, and because the outside room is already pressurized they can be closed again easily.

Maybe I'm just thinking it through too hard. Good SCP though.







