whoa, I totally didn't notice there were comments on this thing.

Well, if you keep it in a room which is already full of water, then you basically need an airlock and scuba gear to deal with the thing at all. If you keep it outside, there is no need for an airlock and no danger of flooding, so the scientists can just open or close the side door as necessary to turn the water on or off.

Actually, why don't they just weld the end doors shut… there's a good afternoon project for someone at site 19.

this SCP has pretty good prank potential. "Hey, Frank, could you grab that box in there?" "Sure." *CLANK* *BLOOOOSH* "AIEEEEEE!"







