One way to explore the cryptoriver to which the boxcar gives access might be to use a tethered ROV with an inertial locator on board. This wouldn't help establish the river's location directly, but it would give clear views of the surrounding rock, which might help narrow it down. And of course the layout could also help that way; if fish live in such rivers, that's another potential clue. If the ROV is tethered, and remember that the tether spools can be over a mile long quite easily, you don't even have to worry about losing it.







